        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 30 at 1:48PM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 148 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Laingsburg, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Corunna and Bancroft around 215 PM EDT.
Durand around 225 PM EDT.
Lennon around 235 PM EDT.

Other locations impacted by this storm include Bennington,
Shaftsburg, and Vernon.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
